messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- controllers/profile.js

Explanation:
- The createProfile handler is implemented in controllers/profile.js as an exported async function named createProfile. It reads profile fields from req.body (name, email, phoneNumber, businessName, contactAddress, logo, website, userId), constructs a new ProfileModel, checks for an existing profile by email, saves the new profile, and returns appropriate HTTP responses (201 on success, 409 if there’s an error or conflict).
- The routes/profile.js file imports createProfile from ../controllers/profile.js and wires it to the POST '/' route, indicating that a POST request to the router’s base path will be handled by createProfile.
